## Step 3 - Let's build the Header
Every website starts with what?(Logo, Navigation)
Instead of using:
<div>
</div>

Use semantic HTML:
<header>
<h2>Ganesh</h2>
</header>
## Because the main page heading (h1) should describe the page content
Your name in the navigation acts more like a site logo

## Step 4 - Navigation
How many pages?
Home
About
Skills
Projects
Contact # Navigation is a list
-> Lists use ul li - Each item links somewhere
-> Links use a

## Build it like this:
<header>
<h2>Ganesh</h2>
<nav>
<ul>
<li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
<li><a href="#">About</a></li>
<li><a href="#">Skills</a></li>
<li><a href="#">Projects</a></li>
<li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
</ul>
</nav>
</header>

header
│
├── h2 (Site Name)
│
└── nav                         This is how you'll see navigation structured in professional projects
     │
     └── ul
          │
          ├── li
          │    │
          │    └── a

